[2] Guinea: 1st case of Ebola in the western mining city of Fria
Date: Wed 17 Dec 2014
Source: Cri Online, Xinhua News Agency report [in French, trans. & summ. Mod.JW, edited]
http://french.cri.cn/621/2014/12/17/441s414300.htm


[The mining city of Fria, in the west of Guinea, has registered its 1st case of Ebola virus disease. The case is a woman, native of Fria, who returned from a stay in Kindia, in Lower Guinea, where she became infected. The woman died on [Tue 16 Dec 2014].

The Russian-owned aluminium mine in Fria closed after a strike more than 2 years ago. - Mod.JW]

