[Reference
----------
Schoepp RJ, Rossi CA, Khan SH, Goba A, Fair JN: Undiagnosed acute viral febrile illnesses, Sierra Leone. Emerg Infect Dis [Internet]. 2014 Jul [date cited]. http://dx.doi.org/10.3201/eid2007.131265

"...most of the Ebola antibodies were against the Zaire strain." That appears to mean they also found antibodies against other Ebola strains such as Sudan. Although the PRNT is generally more specific than the IgM-Elisa test, among ebolaviruses there is considerably cross-reaction even in that test. In any case, they were survivors of unreported infections by hemorrhagic fever ebolaviruses. - Mod.JW]

